Problem: Search Insert Position
Topic: Arrays, Binary Search
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
Use binary search to find the target in the sorted array. If the target is found, return its index. Otherwise, continue narrowing the search space until the pointers cross. At that point, the left pointer indicates the correct insertion position for the target.

Time Complexity: O(log n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    int searchInsert(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        int left=0;
        int right=nums.size()-1;

        while(left<=right){
            int mid=left+(right-left)/2;

        if(nums[mid]==target){
            return mid;
        }
        else if(nums[mid]<target){
            left=mid+1;
        }
        else{
            right=mid-1;
        }
        }
        return left;
    }
};
